The Adjudicator Agent. Receives the Clarity read and the Challenge push-back and resolves them into a final card that names the avoided truth.

Use EXACTLY:
import Anthropic from &quot;@anthropic-ai/sdk&quot;;
const anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY! });

Import these types:
import type { ClarityCard } from &quot;./clarity&quot;;
import type { ChallengeCard } from &quot;./challenge&quot;;

Export this interface:
export interface FinalCard {
  truth: string;
  commitment: string;
  stake: string;
}

Export this function:
export async function adjudicate(
  transcript: string,
  clarity: ClarityCard,
  challenge: ChallengeCard
): Promise&lt;FinalCard&gt;

Implementation:
Call anthropic.messages.create with model &quot;claude-haiku-4-5-20251001&quot;, max_tokens 400.
System: &quot;You are the final voice. You have heard two reads of this situation. Resolve them into one truth the person needs to hear. Be honest. Be specific. Do not soften.&quot;
User: transcript, clarity.read, challenge.avoided, challenge.question combined.
Parse response as JSON: truth (one sentence — the thing this person most needs to hear), commitment (one concrete specific action they can take today), stake (what they risk if they avoid this).
If JSON parse fails return fallback: { truth: &quot;Something important needs your attention.&quot;, commitment: &quot;Name the thing you are avoiding out loud.&quot;, stake: &quot;Continued avoidance.&quot; }

FILE header comment and JSDoc on all exports.

